@startuml recall-consolidate-tandem
' STRUCTURAL overview: how the Recall tier snaps onto the Consolidate tier.
' Recall (pgvector) owns lsn > watermark; Consolidate (S3 FAISS shards) owns
' lsn <= watermark; shard_catalog/consolidated_lsn is the SEAM between them.
' This is a STRUCTURE view -- the step-by-step flows live in the lifecycle,
' consolidation, and query-union SEQUENCE diagrams, not here.
'
' NOTE: "Recall <-> Consolidate" here is the WRITE-FRESHNESS axis. It is a
' DIFFERENT axis from the SSD-cache "hot/cold" storage-distance axis in
' ssd-cache-tiers.puml -- do not conflate them. The SSD/RAM cache holds
' disposable copies of consolidated shards and never affects completeness.

title RosalindDB: the Recall tier snapped onto the Consolidate tier (structure)

left to right direction

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam wrapWidth 200
skinparam nodesep 25
skinparam ranksep 55

actor "client" as client

component "cp\n(control plane)" as cp
component "query_dp\n(union + merge)" as dp
component "index_builder\n(consolidation worker)" as builder

package "Write-freshness axis" {
  database "Recall tier\npgvector\nowns lsn > watermark" as recall
  rectangle "shard_catalog /\nconsolidated_lsn\n= the WATERMARK (seam)" as catalog #LightYellow
  cloud "Consolidate tier\nS3 FAISS shards\nowns lsn <= watermark" as os
}

' ---- control plane fans out to the two data-plane workers ----
client --> cp
cp --> dp
cp --> recall : write (sync)

' ---- consolidation worker: drain Recall, build shard, advance watermark ----
builder --> recall : drain
builder --> os : build shard
builder --> catalog : advance watermark

' ---- query: read watermark, then search both sides of the seam ----
dp --> catalog : read watermark
dp --> recall : search lsn > wm
dp --> os : search lsn <= wm

' keep the seam laid out BETWEEN the two tiers (left-to-right rank order)
recall -[hidden]down-> catalog
catalog -[hidden]down-> os

note bottom of os
  Partition rule: the watermark splits every
  vector by its single lsn --
    lsn <= W  -> Consolidate
    lsn >  W  -> Recall
  Exactly one tier each, so the union is
  complete (no gap, no overlap).
end note

@enduml
